        "text": "[[Relationalize Property]]: \n Direct land management: acquiring land and renting it to established or future farmers in the long run; taking good care of the natural environment (natural resources, land, landscapes); managing buildings;\n-  Land stewardship: acquiring land and keeping it in agricultural use while being respectful of the environment; working with local authorities to develop sustainable farming practices and land stewardship; advocacy work\nLa Foncière collects savings (shares of €103, Une action = 103€ avec déduction fiscale de 9%) from the public who adhere to values and goals set in the [[Terre de Liens Founding Charter]]; it then buys agricultural land and buildings, which are rented out to farmers on long-term leases.\ncquisition par TDL : ils sont accueillis, préparés et instruits par les bénévoles, avec l’appui des permanents régionaux.  \nLike the Foncière, it then rents the farms it has acquired to farmers. It also has a more general mission of informing and mobilising citizens and other stakeholders."
